1
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:13,067
<i>Would you give your life
for someone you don't know?</i>

2
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:15,667
<i> Not for them but for you.</i>

3
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:17,367
<i> Daga, there's still hope.</i>

4
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:18,500
<i> They're going to surrender!</i>

5
00:00:19,900 --> 00:00:21,733
<i> Amo! Amo!</i>

6
00:00:21,867 --> 00:00:23,233
<i> Don't hurt them, okay?</i>

7
00:00:23,367 --> 00:00:25,533
<i>You won't regret your decision,
Daga.</i>

8
00:00:25,667 --> 00:00:28,767
<i>I really hope his connection to
our cases is just a coincidence.</i>

9
00:00:28,900 --> 00:00:30,733
<i>When you have wishful thinking.</i>

10
00:00:30,867 --> 00:00:33,233
<i>That's when your bias in
the investigation comes in.</i>

11
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:34,933
<i> Very entertaining!</i>

12
00:00:35,067 --> 00:00:37,700
<i>It's becoming very interesting.</i>

13
00:00:37,833 --> 00:00:39,133
<i>That's how it is when you
investigate.</i>

14
00:00:39,267 --> 00:00:42,967
<i>The questions develop
as you get closer to the truth.</i>

15
00:00:43,100 --> 00:00:44,367
<i> Do I understand you correctly?</i>

16
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:47,200
<i>Just give you best in acting,
and then I'll take care of it.</i>

17
00:00:47,333 --> 00:00:49,633
<i>Victor's drama is really
effective.</i>

18
00:00:49,767 --> 00:00:51,300
<i>You've been in politics
for a long time</i>

19
00:00:51,433 --> 00:00:54,967
<i>but it seems like you've only
just found a worthy opponent.</i>

20
00:00:55,100 --> 00:00:56,167
<i> Oh my, never mind.</i>

21
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:58,567
<i>Maybe our countrymen will think
I'm trying to brag.</i>

22
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:00,767
<i>We really should give
a shout-out</i>

23
00:01:00,900 --> 00:01:03,400
<i>to those who responded
to the riot.</i>

24
00:01:03,533 --> 00:01:05,567
<i>Sergeant Enriquez
and Lieutenant Conde.</i>

25
00:01:05,700 --> 00:01:06,567
<i> Sergeant!</i>

26
00:01:06,700 --> 00:01:07,767
<i> Conde!</i>

27
00:01:16,267 --> 00:01:17,833
- Hi, Glenn.
- Mom.

28
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:19,900
Have you seen this?

29
00:01:21,100 --> 00:01:23,333
You have good soldiers here,
Major.

30
00:01:23,467 --> 00:01:28,100
You are the real superheroes
of today.

31
00:01:28,233 --> 00:01:30,367
Why don't you give yourselves
a round of applause?

32
00:01:30,500 --> 00:01:31,467
You deserve it!

33
00:01:33,567 --> 00:01:35,400
Godfather Victor is something
else.

34
00:01:35,533 --> 00:01:39,533
He's really maximizing the hero
narrative to the last drop.

35
00:01:39,667 --> 00:01:41,133
Of course.

36
00:01:41,300 --> 00:01:43,267
Best to ride the wave.

37
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:44,433
Right, Glen?

38
00:01:44,567 --> 00:01:46,133
You know what's funny, Mom?

39
00:01:46,267 --> 00:01:48,667
This is really a battle of
public perception, isn't it?

40
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:53,467
Well, your daddy already knows
that.

41
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:55,300
He's not used to it yet.

42
00:01:55,433 --> 00:01:56,900
I have an idea.

43
00:01:57,033 --> 00:02:00,667
There's something I can tell
Daddy to make up

44
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:02,500
for in the polls.

45
00:02:02,633 --> 00:02:03,867
I hope he'll listen to me.

46
00:02:05,033 --> 00:02:08,100
I will make him listen to you,
son.

47
00:02:25,533 --> 00:02:26,900
Thank you, Sergeant.

48
00:02:28,867 --> 00:02:30,233
Thank you very much.

49
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:34,600
Conde.

50
00:02:40,767 --> 00:02:41,867
Excuse me, Sir.

51
00:02:46,767 --> 00:02:48,067
It's here Amo.

52
00:02:48,233 --> 00:02:50,000
Bring it here.

53
00:02:51,167 --> 00:02:52,400
Yes, by the way.

54
00:02:52,533 --> 00:02:55,300
We've brought some snacks
for you.

55
00:02:57,367 --> 00:03:00,400
Wait, wait! Just wait!
Amo, how about my products?

56
00:03:00,533 --> 00:03:01,600
No one will buy it anymore?

57
00:03:01,733 --> 00:03:03,167
You, don't worry.

58
00:03:03,300 --> 00:03:04,967
We'll buy it all.

59
00:03:05,100 --> 00:03:08,400
- Go and buy all her products.
- Amo, you're my idol!

60
00:03:08,533 --> 00:03:10,200
- Thank you!
- Let's eat that too!

61
00:03:10,333 --> 00:03:12,167
Take that with you.

62
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:16,467
- Hey, eating time!
- Dude, help me!

63
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:20,467
Let's go, let's go!

64
00:03:21,967 --> 00:03:23,600
Let's take a photo.

65
00:03:23,733 --> 00:03:25,100
Let's include Major.

66
00:03:25,233 --> 00:03:26,233
Okay.

67
00:03:27,467 --> 00:03:29,267
Thank you, thank you.

68
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:31,000
Thank you too,
thank you too.

69
00:03:31,133 --> 00:03:32,567
Have a snack first.

70
00:03:32,700 --> 00:03:33,633
Sit down.

71
00:03:35,567 --> 00:03:36,633
I'll go ahead.

72
00:03:36,767 --> 00:03:38,700
Okay, I'll walk you out.

73
00:03:45,367 --> 00:03:46,467
Enriquez.

74
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:49,567
I already took some food
for us before we even started.

75
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,433
No, Sir, I'm fine.

76
00:03:55,200 --> 00:03:56,367
Amo is something else, right?

77
00:03:56,933 --> 00:03:58,467
He is very famous now.

78
00:03:58,600 --> 00:04:02,033
Did you see the ones in the
comment section on social media?

79
00:04:02,167 --> 00:04:03,500
He's the number one.

80
00:04:04,567 --> 00:04:07,667
How about you, even though
he's your number one suspect,

81
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:09,067
will you vote for him?

82
00:04:11,067 --> 00:04:12,567
I don't know yet, Sir.

83
00:04:13,700 --> 00:04:17,267
You know as for me,
after what happened today,

84
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:19,633
I'm sure I'll vote for him.

85
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:23,133
What?

86
00:04:23,267 --> 00:04:24,200
Should I get you some?

87
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:26,467
Sir, thank you.

88
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:27,567
I'll just get some.

89
00:05:01,933 --> 00:05:04,567
Thank you very much, Sir Amo.

90
00:05:04,700 --> 00:05:06,767
Thank you very much, Major.

91
00:05:06,900 --> 00:05:09,733
If there's anything else
I can help you with,

92
00:05:09,867 --> 00:05:10,700
just let me know, okay?

93
00:05:10,833 --> 00:05:11,433
Okay.

94
00:05:12,567 --> 00:05:13,433
Take care.

95
00:05:13,567 --> 00:05:14,433
Okay.

96
00:05:17,767 --> 00:05:19,267
Okay, follow him.

97
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:23,300
Just keep your distance, okay,
so we won't be noticed.

98
00:05:23,433 --> 00:05:24,700
Okay, Mayor.

99
00:05:53,067 --> 00:05:55,600
What's Victor doing here?

100
00:06:03,033 --> 00:06:04,200
Just stay here, okay?

101
00:06:05,333 --> 00:06:08,200
I'll see what is Victor's
purpose here.

102
00:06:15,400 --> 00:06:18,033
You take care of Daga's
families.

103
00:06:23,433 --> 00:06:24,100
Why?

104
00:06:25,133 --> 00:06:26,500
Is there a problem?

105
00:06:26,633 --> 00:06:30,033
You know, I understand your
strategy for using Daga.

106
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:33,533
I can see it from
the survey results.

107
00:06:33,667 --> 00:06:35,367
But my fear is,

108
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:38,867
Daga might turn against us
someday and betray us.

109
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:42,600
This money you gave,

110
00:06:42,767 --> 00:06:44,867
you know that when this is gone,
Daga's family will extort money

111
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,033
from you for the rest of your
life.

112
00:06:46,167 --> 00:06:47,267
You know that.

113
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:49,833
You're not going to let
that happen, right?

114
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:54,733
Do you understand
what I'm saying?

115
00:06:54,867 --> 00:06:56,333
Loud and clear, Boss.

116
00:06:56,467 --> 00:06:57,867
Loud and clear.

117
00:07:27,700 --> 00:07:30,300
You'll have a day with me too,
Victor.

118
00:07:31,667 --> 00:07:32,800
When?

119
00:07:36,700 --> 00:07:38,633
Good Evening, Victor.

120
00:07:39,833 --> 00:07:41,167
What are you doing here?

121
00:07:41,300 --> 00:07:43,500
I should be asking you that.

122
00:07:44,567 --> 00:07:45,967
Who were you talking to earlier?

123
00:07:47,100 --> 00:07:48,767
I'm sorry, Joaquin.

124
00:07:48,933 --> 00:07:50,933
I can't answer your question.

125
00:07:52,067 --> 00:07:55,300
You, why are you following me?

126
00:07:55,433 --> 00:08:01,033
Well, I was going to talk
to you about your gimmick.

127
00:08:01,167 --> 00:08:05,267
Your charisma is different
imagine,

128
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:09,667
I left showbiz to you.

129
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:16,133
Now, you want to get involved
in politics?

130
00:08:18,900 --> 00:08:25,400
Buddy, do you mean I'll let you
lose without a bloody fight?

131
00:08:26,633 --> 00:08:28,767
I'm not expecting you to.

132
00:08:28,900 --> 00:08:30,233
We are comrades.

133
00:08:31,533 --> 00:08:34,367
I know you know who you're up
against.

134
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:36,233
Buddy, I'll give you a chance.

135
00:08:37,733 --> 00:08:40,800
While there's still time,
just back out.

136
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:46,033
And if I don't want to,
what will you do?

137
00:08:46,167 --> 00:08:51,467
Well, we'll just cross
the bridge when we get there.

138
00:09:11,933 --> 00:09:14,767
Your idol is something, Bobby?

139
00:09:14,900 --> 00:09:15,900
True.

140
00:09:16,033 --> 00:09:18,433
That's why I'm voting for Amo.

141
00:09:18,567 --> 00:09:20,867
You guys, it seems like you
don't watch teleseryes.

142
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,867
What are you saying there, Mar?

143
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,233
You see.

144
00:09:24,367 --> 00:09:26,933
Amo's ratings suddenly went up.

145
00:09:27,067 --> 00:09:30,067
It seems it's scripted,
it doesn't seem genuine.

146
00:09:30,233 --> 00:09:31,633
You're so negative.

147
00:09:31,767 --> 00:09:32,667
Delicious!

148
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:33,633
Winner!

149
00:09:33,767 --> 00:09:35,700
Boss Tonyo,
thanks for the food trip.

150
00:09:35,833 --> 00:09:36,900
- It's delicious.
- Yes, boss.

151
00:09:37,033 --> 00:09:39,767
Just let us know if we can help
with the investigation.

152
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:40,633
We can handle it.

153
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:48,433
Maybe you've heard something
about the gang members involved?

154
00:09:50,433 --> 00:09:51,833
It doesn't seem like there's
anything else, Boss.

155
00:09:51,967 --> 00:09:53,067
What, is there something?

156
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:53,900
Nothing, Boss.

157
00:09:54,033 --> 00:09:56,200
I can't remember if there's more

158
00:09:56,333 --> 00:09:58,200
because we've watched it all
on video.

159
00:09:58,333 --> 00:10:00,267
And I haven't heard of any
gangsters there, Boss, nothing.

160
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:01,433
Negative, Boss.

161
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:02,833
- This is delicious.
- Nothing?

162
00:10:02,967 --> 00:10:08,267
Boss, maybe we could ask
for something to drink, right?

163
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:11,633
Even this or sodas.

164
00:10:11,767 --> 00:10:13,733
Do you want me to push you?

165
00:10:13,867 --> 00:10:16,100
You don't have any information
to give me.

166
00:10:16,233 --> 00:10:17,300
You're something else.

167
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:23,067
With the gang, nothing,
but with the poison, there is.

168
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:24,600
Actually, Grandmother,

169
00:10:24,733 --> 00:10:27,000
I also thought about what Mar
was saying.

170
00:10:28,033 --> 00:10:30,133
I've already converted someone,
haven't I?

171
00:10:30,267 --> 00:10:31,967
I already have an ally here.

172
00:10:32,100 --> 00:10:33,933
Is it true that you've
turned your back, Bobby?

173
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:36,100
I don't know.

174
00:10:36,233 --> 00:10:37,767
My gut feeling is really
different.

175
00:10:37,900 --> 00:10:40,733
It seems like what happened
was too perfect.

176
00:10:40,867 --> 00:10:42,933
And you're right
that his ratings went up.

177
00:10:43,067 --> 00:10:46,133
Because in our precinct,
almost everyone has converted.

178
00:10:46,267 --> 00:10:47,700
Well if you give them
a roasted pig,

179
00:10:47,833 --> 00:10:50,600
most likely many police officers
will believe you.

180
00:10:50,733 --> 00:10:54,067
It's up to you.
As for me, I don't like Amo.

181
00:10:54,200 --> 00:10:55,467
Too much showbiz.

182
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:57,033
There's already been
a rumor before

183
00:10:57,167 --> 00:10:58,333
that he abandoned his son,
right?

184
00:10:58,467 --> 00:10:59,567
He seems like a womanizer.

185
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:02,133
Hey, Mar, that's been an issue
for a long time!

186
00:11:02,267 --> 00:11:04,733
Besides, it's been proven
that it's not true.

187
00:11:04,867 --> 00:11:09,067
Oh my, it's not like
Joaquin Guerrero is a womanizer.

188
00:11:09,233 --> 00:11:11,200
When they're just the same.

189
00:11:11,333 --> 00:11:13,900
Well, at least El Hepe
has a good family.

190
00:11:14,033 --> 00:11:16,400
With Amo, none,
he doesn't have a family.

191
00:11:17,533 --> 00:11:20,067
Oh my, let's just eat.

192
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:21,200
That's right.

193
00:11:21,333 --> 00:11:22,500
We'll still be full.

194
00:11:23,533 --> 00:11:24,600
What about the poison?

195
00:11:25,900 --> 00:11:28,800
This bread looks delicious
and this rice cake.

196
00:11:28,933 --> 00:11:29,733
Gulaman!

197
00:11:29,867 --> 00:11:31,867
Rice, and other dishes
for breakfast.

198
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:33,367
All right, take whatever you
want there.

199
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:34,533
I'll take care of it.

200
00:11:34,667 --> 00:11:36,433
Five hamburgers.

201
00:11:36,567 --> 00:11:37,367
Guys, save some for me.

202
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:38,633
Hey, what about the poison?

203
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:42,833
Aren't you looking for
someone to buy poison on

204
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:44,033
the black market?

205
00:11:44,167 --> 00:11:45,367
We've found a contact.

206
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:48,300
But just be careful, Boss.

207
00:11:49,367 --> 00:11:50,067
Why?

208
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:54,633
This world you're about
to enter is a bit dangerous.

209
00:11:56,967 --> 00:11:59,200
All right, Boss,
let me eat first?

210
00:12:00,267 --> 00:12:03,767
Buddy, this, this,
this is mine.

211
00:12:03,900 --> 00:12:05,167
There's a lot of it!

212
00:12:05,300 --> 00:12:06,733
Of course,
let's take all of that.

213
00:12:15,133 --> 00:12:16,100
What is it, Ma'am?

214
00:12:17,867 --> 00:12:21,133
Don't tell me you're looking
for Amo's connection

215
00:12:21,267 --> 00:12:22,967
to those three cases through
gossip?

216
00:12:23,100 --> 00:12:24,400
Noble,

217
00:12:24,533 --> 00:12:28,567
did you hear the allegation
that Amo abandoned his child?

218
00:12:28,700 --> 00:12:30,333
Just now.

219
00:12:30,467 --> 00:12:35,100
But if it's true, so what,
right?

220
00:12:35,233 --> 00:12:36,800
He's not alone.

221
00:12:41,667 --> 00:12:42,667
Just kidding.

222
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:43,600
Sorry.

223
00:12:46,100 --> 00:12:47,533
What are you going
to find there?

224
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:49,100
I don't really know yet,

225
00:12:49,233 --> 00:12:54,200
but Lieutenant Conde told me
that in an investigation,

226
00:12:54,333 --> 00:12:57,267
you have to be willing to change
your questions

227
00:12:57,400 --> 00:12:58,633
to get the real answer.

228
00:13:00,167 --> 00:13:03,300
That's all. Right now,
I just want to know if the rumor

229
00:13:03,433 --> 00:13:05,333
that Amo abandoned his child
is true.

230
00:13:05,467 --> 00:13:06,967
Let me clarify, okay?

231
00:13:07,100 --> 00:13:11,400
You mean, after everything
Amo did yesterday,

232
00:13:11,533 --> 00:13:13,100
you still suspect him?

233
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:16,267
Answer me, Noble.

234
00:13:17,500 --> 00:13:20,800
Based on the connections
I found in Amo's movie,

235
00:13:20,933 --> 00:13:24,033
can you say that 100 percent,
he had nothing to do with it,

236
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:25,533
not even the slightest bit?

237
00:13:25,667 --> 00:13:28,500
You told me that Amo
and I were close!

238
00:13:28,633 --> 00:13:30,867
Look at our pictures.
We're so close!

239
00:13:32,300 --> 00:13:34,533
You never get tired of taking
pictures with Amo

240
00:13:34,667 --> 00:13:35,967
over and over again, right,
Garcia?

241
00:13:36,100 --> 00:13:37,900
I told you that we're close.

242
00:13:38,033 --> 00:13:41,567
And his comeback movie,
Baby Amo's Son and Te Amo,

243
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:42,933
he's going to take me with him.

244
00:13:43,067 --> 00:13:45,300
This, there it is.

245
00:13:45,433 --> 00:13:47,933
This picture, it's new.

246
00:13:48,067 --> 00:13:50,967
A picture of us at Lara's
funeral.

247
00:13:51,100 --> 00:13:52,533
Amo.

248
00:13:52,667 --> 00:13:53,933
Oh, right?

249
00:13:54,067 --> 00:13:54,733
There it is.

250
00:13:56,567 --> 00:13:58,900
There it is, we met again.

251
00:14:02,900 --> 00:14:08,333
Did Amo go to Lieutenant Conde's
girlfriend's funeral?

252
00:14:08,467 --> 00:14:11,833
Maybe he is really
that supportive?

253
00:14:11,967 --> 00:14:16,033
Did he also visit the wake
of your mentor, Ma'am Dina?

254
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:19,533
No.

255
00:14:34,133 --> 00:14:37,867
Bro, I hope this intel you
got will lead us somewhere.

256
00:14:39,467 --> 00:14:41,800
When we find out who killed
Sonny,

257
00:14:43,467 --> 00:14:45,867
we can possibly solve the museum
robbery as well

258
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,967
as the San Isidro case.

259
00:14:49,100 --> 00:14:51,333
You'll also find out who killed
Lara.

260
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:00,133
Hello?

261
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:02,267
Yes, Sir.

262
00:15:02,433 --> 00:15:03,933
Hello, Conde.
Where are you?

263
00:15:04,067 --> 00:15:06,833
We're just following a lead
about the poison, Sir.

264
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:09,833
Is there a problem?

265
00:15:09,967 --> 00:15:11,667
There's no problem.

266
00:15:11,800 --> 00:15:16,600
But I have a feeling
Sergeant Enriquez

267
00:15:16,733 --> 00:15:19,100
won't let go of his angle
about Amo.

268
00:15:22,033 --> 00:15:24,600
Enriquez seems really stubborn,
Sir.

269
00:15:24,733 --> 00:15:26,367
Just keep an eye on her, Conde.

270
00:15:26,500 --> 00:15:27,767
It's too risky.

271
00:15:27,900 --> 00:15:31,467
She might find out Amo is your
father.

272
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:34,033
It might look like there's
a conflict of interest

273
00:15:34,167 --> 00:15:35,467
even though there isn't.

274
00:15:35,633 --> 00:15:37,500
Okay, be careful.

275
00:15:37,633 --> 00:15:39,700
Yes, Sir. Okay,
I'll take care of it.

276
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:45,600
Come on.

277
00:15:45,733 --> 00:15:46,800
Let's go there.

278
00:16:48,433 --> 00:16:49,667
Good morning.

279
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:52,333
We just wanted to ask you
something.

280
00:16:52,467 --> 00:16:53,900
We just wanted to know if...

281
00:16:54,033 --> 00:16:54,967
You're police officers, right?

282
00:16:56,233 --> 00:16:57,400
You know, just leave.

283
00:17:00,233 --> 00:17:00,867
Bro...

284
00:17:31,933 --> 00:17:39,900
Amo and the Spirits.

285
00:17:47,033 --> 00:17:48,567
Hey, they look alike.

286
00:17:53,100 --> 00:17:54,933
<i>Amo is very impressive,
isn't he?</i>

287
00:17:55,067 --> 00:17:57,167
<i>He interfered in the police
operation.</i>

288
00:17:57,300 --> 00:17:58,200
<i> Is that impressive?</i>

289
00:17:58,333 --> 00:17:59,600
<i> I don't like Amo.</i>

290
00:17:59,733 --> 00:18:00,600
<i>There's already a rumor,
isn't there,</i>

291
00:18:00,733 --> 00:18:01,867
<i> that a child was abandoned?</i>

292
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:05,033
<i> Our picture at Lara's wake.</i>

293
00:18:05,167 --> 00:18:06,200
<i> That's Amo.</i>

294
00:18:08,833 --> 00:18:11,067
We're not looking for trouble.

295
00:18:11,200 --> 00:18:13,700
We just want to find out
where Mr. Teban is.

296
00:18:15,733 --> 00:18:17,000
He's a police officer.

297
00:18:17,133 --> 00:18:19,067
You won't get out of here alive.

298
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:20,400
Hit him!

299
00:18:40,067 --> 00:18:41,767
Ma'am, what are you doing there?

300
00:18:41,900 --> 00:18:44,733
Why are you taking a picture
of Lieutenant Conde?

301
00:18:46,033 --> 00:18:46,767
Noble...

302
00:18:49,067 --> 00:18:50,800
Look at this.

303
00:18:50,933 --> 00:18:53,600
Don't Amo and Lieutenant Conde
look alike?

304
00:18:53,733 --> 00:18:55,933
Yes, they do look alike.

305
00:18:57,567 --> 00:18:59,267
- Could it be that...
- What, Ma'am...

306
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:01,000
That they related?

307
00:19:01,133 --> 00:19:02,400
That's my hunch.

308
00:19:05,100 --> 00:19:07,533
Based on the interaction
between the two of them.

309
00:19:07,667 --> 00:19:11,300
And you remember the rumor,
'that I told you...

310
00:19:11,433 --> 00:19:13,333
that Amo had an abandoned child?

311
00:19:13,467 --> 00:19:15,100
And why would Amo visit

312
00:19:15,233 --> 00:19:18,867
Lieutenant Conde's girlfriend's
wake, right?

313
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:23,000
And most of all, this,
there you go.

314
00:19:23,133 --> 00:19:25,067
They look exactly alike.

315
00:19:27,167 --> 00:19:28,200
A bit.

316
00:19:29,700 --> 00:19:31,500
But because Ma'am...

317
00:19:32,733 --> 00:19:34,967
Noble, you don't believe me.

318
00:19:36,167 --> 00:19:37,933
It's not like that, Ma'am.

319
00:19:38,067 --> 00:19:40,333
I just don't know what
connection this has

320
00:19:40,467 --> 00:19:42,367
to the cases we're
investigating.

321
00:19:42,500 --> 00:19:45,500
I'll just see where this hunch
takes me.

322
00:20:38,167 --> 00:20:38,967
What?

323
00:20:39,100 --> 00:20:40,367
Put your hands up!

324
00:20:41,567 --> 00:20:44,200
I said put your hands up!

325
00:20:44,333 --> 00:20:45,733
Put your gun down?

326
00:20:46,867 --> 00:20:48,133
We're not afraid of that.

327
00:20:51,267 --> 00:20:53,000
All I need is Ka Teban.

328
00:20:54,100 --> 00:20:55,067
Me.

329
00:20:56,800 --> 00:20:58,033
I'm Ka Teban.

330
00:21:14,667 --> 00:21:16,533
Enriquez, hey.

331
00:21:16,667 --> 00:21:18,300
It's Amo you're looking at.

332
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:21,300
That's okay, that's okay.

333
00:21:21,433 --> 00:21:26,433
I know you really like Tisoy,
pointed noses,

334
00:21:26,567 --> 00:21:29,800
those puffy eyes,
strong sex appeal, you know.

335
00:21:32,100 --> 00:21:35,100
Enriquez, do you want
to have dinner tonight?

336
00:21:35,233 --> 00:21:35,933
My treat.

337
00:21:37,500 --> 00:21:39,367
I'm going home,
Lieutenant Garcia.

338
00:21:39,500 --> 00:21:40,967
You're too formal.

339
00:21:41,100 --> 00:21:43,167
It's like we have no past.

340
00:21:43,333 --> 00:21:47,000
First name basis only.
Just call me Eric.

341
00:21:48,267 --> 00:21:50,067
Is there anything else you need,
Sir Eric?

342
00:21:51,667 --> 00:21:53,233
I don't have anything, but you,

343
00:21:53,367 --> 00:21:55,067
it looks like you need
to unwind.

344
00:21:55,200 --> 00:21:57,667
And it's your lucky day today

345
00:21:57,800 --> 00:22:00,667
because I want to invite you
too.

346
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:03,533
So do you want to have dinner
with me? My treat.

347
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:06,933
Wait a minute.

348
00:22:07,067 --> 00:22:10,067
Why are you so focused on Amo?

349
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:16,767
Don't tell me
you're into older guys.

350
00:22:20,167 --> 00:22:21,733
Sir, look at him.

351
00:22:21,867 --> 00:22:23,500
He looks like Lieutenant Conde,
right?

352
00:22:26,800 --> 00:22:27,767
Let me see.

353
00:22:29,033 --> 00:22:30,333
No way!

354
00:22:30,467 --> 00:22:32,067
I look more like Amo.

355
00:22:33,433 --> 00:22:34,100
- Look at his nose.
- No way!

356
00:22:34,233 --> 00:22:35,633
Amo is so handsome.

357
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:39,833
So are you saying I'm ugly?

358
00:22:40,867 --> 00:22:42,300
It's not like that, Sir.

359
00:22:43,333 --> 00:22:45,733
I knew it. You find me handsome.

360
00:22:45,867 --> 00:22:48,267
So, let's go have dinner
tonight.

361
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:50,400
7 PM, I'll pick you up?

362
00:22:52,333 --> 00:22:54,700
Why do they look so much alike?

363
00:22:54,833 --> 00:22:56,533
Are they related?

364
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:01,100
Boss.

365
00:23:01,233 --> 00:23:04,633
Put that on your nose to get rid
of the swelling.

366
00:23:04,767 --> 00:23:08,167
Sorry about the locals.

367
00:23:08,300 --> 00:23:09,567
We're just paranoid

368
00:23:09,700 --> 00:23:11,567
when it comes to dealing
with the police.

369
00:23:13,133 --> 00:23:16,400
We don't care what kind of
racket you're up to here.

370
00:23:16,533 --> 00:23:18,433
We came here for something else.

371
00:23:18,567 --> 00:23:20,033
How would we know?

372
00:23:20,167 --> 00:23:21,933
We don't know you.

373
00:23:22,567 --> 00:23:24,733
How did you find me?

374
00:23:26,533 --> 00:23:31,200
From our informant
but believe me, Ka Teban,

375
00:23:31,333 --> 00:23:33,233
we just want to ask you
something.

376
00:23:33,367 --> 00:23:34,867
About what?

377
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:37,800
Where do you get strychnine
poison?

378
00:23:39,333 --> 00:23:40,400
Strychnine?

379
00:23:41,433 --> 00:23:43,300
Why are you asking about it?

380
00:23:43,433 --> 00:23:47,400
That's the only lead we have in
the case we're investigating.

381
00:23:47,533 --> 00:23:50,167
That's why we want to know
where we can get it.

382
00:23:50,300 --> 00:23:54,033
You know, back in the day,
it was easy to get it

383
00:23:54,167 --> 00:23:57,733
because it was one of the
ingredients in rat poison.

384
00:23:57,900 --> 00:24:00,700
But now, it's been banned
for a long time

385
00:24:00,833 --> 00:24:03,633
because it's too dangerous,
especially for humans.

386
00:24:04,700 --> 00:24:07,133
There's no strychnine
circulating anymore,

387
00:24:07,267 --> 00:24:08,667
not even on the black market.

388
00:24:08,800 --> 00:24:11,000
But, Sir, for example,
I really need it.

389
00:24:12,300 --> 00:24:14,500
Where can I get it?

390
00:24:14,633 --> 00:24:17,033
You'll probably ship it
from another country.

391
00:24:17,167 --> 00:24:19,667
But before you can do that,

392
00:24:19,800 --> 00:24:23,500
you need your contacts
to be very wide.

393
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:28,067
So if I were you, Chief,
you'd be careful.

394
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:31,233
What you're investigating
is very dangerous.

395
00:24:41,100 --> 00:24:42,800
Ma'am is such a beautiful
police officer.

396
00:24:42,933 --> 00:24:45,633
Do you know that because
of you disrespecting me?

397
00:24:45,767 --> 00:24:47,333
You could go to jail
for six months.

398
00:24:47,467 --> 00:24:50,800
If you only had a boyfriend,
no one would be rude to you.

399
00:24:50,933 --> 00:24:53,333
Your smile is really beautiful,
baby.

400
00:24:53,467 --> 00:24:56,267
- You're so handsome!
- You have no shame!

401
00:24:56,400 --> 00:24:57,367
Your face is so thick!

402
00:24:57,500 --> 00:24:58,900
That's enough!

403
00:24:59,033 --> 00:25:00,567
Even if you turn the situation
around,

404
00:25:00,700 --> 00:25:02,900
it's wrong to hurt your wife.

405
00:25:03,067 --> 00:25:03,700
Sir Tonyo!

406
00:25:03,833 --> 00:25:05,300
That's Tonyo.

407
00:25:05,433 --> 00:25:07,200
Tonyo, my loves...

408
00:25:07,333 --> 00:25:08,800
Your body is big, Sir.

409
00:25:08,933 --> 00:25:11,567
Grandmother,
I'm here with Lieutenant Conde.

410
00:25:11,700 --> 00:25:12,933
I'm telling you...

411
00:25:13,067 --> 00:25:14,367
I'll be careful.

412
00:25:14,500 --> 00:25:17,967
Don't be careful!
I want to have a grandchild!

413
00:25:20,067 --> 00:25:23,300
You know, even if I disappear
from your life,

414
00:25:23,433 --> 00:25:24,500
Tonyo, you're still happy.

415
00:25:24,633 --> 00:25:26,333
Don't worry, Lara.

416
00:25:26,467 --> 00:25:27,900
I won't leave, Sir.
